 2131, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2255, \"end\": 2262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7213593360064274, \"rank\": 0.38578163733415927, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"the joint-most successful team\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic men's football history\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"three gold medals\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2241}, {\"ngram\": \"this stage\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men's football at the Olympics is primarily capped at under-23 players, with only three \\\"over-age\\\" exceptions allowed as the tournament aims to focus on giving a platform to up-and-coming stars.\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Men's football\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"under-23 players\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2387}, {\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"the tournament\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"a platform\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2487}, {\"ngram\": \"stars\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A GB squad could therefore have handed players likeJarrad Branthwaite,Adam Wharton, and Brennan Johnson some international minutes this summer - but alas, it was not to be once again.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2515, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.788291153273264, \"rank\": 0.26856681804365756, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 26